4444  WhenPerformedBound(solver()->MakeActionDemon(std::move(action)));
4445  }
4446 #endif // SWIG
4447 
4448  // Attaches a demon awakened when anything about this interval changes.
4449  void WhenAnything(Demon* const d);
4450  // Attaches a closure awakened when anything about this interval changes.
4451  void WhenAnything(Solver::Closure closure) {
4452  WhenAnything(solver()->MakeClosureDemon(std::move(closure)));
4453  }
4454 #if !defined(SWIG)
4455  // Attaches an action awakened when anything about this interval changes.
4456  void WhenAnything(Solver::Action action) {
4457  WhenAnything(solver()->MakeActionDemon(std::move(action)));
4458  }
4459 #endif // SWIG
4460 
4461  // These methods create expressions encapsulating the start, end
4462  // and duration of the interval var. Please note that these must not
4463  // be used if the interval var is unperformed.
4464  virtual IntExpr* StartExpr() = 0;
4465  virtual IntExpr* DurationExpr() = 0;
4466  virtual IntExpr* EndExpr() = 0;
4467  virtual IntExpr* PerformedExpr() = 0;
4468  // These methods create expressions encapsulating the start, end
4469  // and duration of the interval var. If the interval var is
4470  // unperformed, they will return the unperformed_value.
4471  virtual IntExpr* SafeStartExpr(int64 unperformed_value) = 0;
4472  virtual IntExpr* SafeDurationExpr(int64 unperformed_value) = 0;
4473  virtual IntExpr* SafeEndExpr(int64 unperformed_value) = 0;
4474 
4475  // Accepts the given visitor.
4476  virtual void Accept(ModelVisitor* const visitor) const = 0;
4477 
4478  private:
4479  DISALLOW_COPY_AND_ASSIGN(IntervalVar);
4480 };
4481 
4482 // ----- SequenceVar -----
4483 
4484 // A sequence variable is a variable whose domain is a set of possible
4485 // orderings of the interval variables. It allows ordering of tasks. It
4486 // has two sets of methods: ComputePossibleFirstsAndLasts(), which
4487 // returns the list of interval variables that can be ranked first or
4488 // last; and RankFirst/RankNotFirst/RankLast/RankNotLast, which can be
4489 // used to create the search decision.
4490 class SequenceVar : public PropagationBaseObject {
4491  public:
4492  SequenceVar(Solver* const s, const std::vector<IntervalVar*>& intervals,
4493  const std::vector<IntVar*>& nexts, const std::string& name);
4494 
4495  ~SequenceVar() override;
4496 
4497  std::string DebugString() const override;
4498 
4499 #if !defined(SWIG)
4500  // Returns the minimum and maximum duration of combined interval
4501  // vars in the sequence.
4502  void DurationRange(int64* const dmin, int64* const dmax) const;
4503 
4504  // Returns the minimum start min and the maximum end max of all
4505  // interval vars in the sequence.
4506  void HorizonRange(int64* const hmin, int64* const hmax) const;
4507 
4508  // Returns the minimum start min and the maximum end max of all
4509  // unranked interval vars in the sequence.
4510  void ActiveHorizonRange(int64* const hmin, int64* const hmax) const;
4511 
4512  // Compute statistics on the sequence.
4513  void ComputeStatistics(int* const ranked, int* const not_ranked,
4514  int* const unperformed) const;
4515 #endif // !defined(SWIG)
4516 
4517  // Ranks the index_th interval var first of all unranked interval
4518  // vars. After that, it will no longer be considered ranked.
4519  void RankFirst(int index);
4520 
4521  // Indicates that the index_th interval var will not be ranked first
4522  // of all currently unranked interval vars.
4523  void RankNotFirst(int index);
4524 
4525  // Ranks the index_th interval var first of all unranked interval
4526  // vars. After that, it will no longer be considered ranked.
4527  void RankLast(int index);
4528 
4529  // Indicates that the index_th interval var will not be ranked first
4530  // of all currently unranked interval vars.
4531  void RankNotLast(int index);
4532 
4533  // Computes the set of indices of interval variables that can be
4534  // ranked first in the set of unranked activities.
4535  void ComputePossibleFirstsAndLasts(std::vector<int>* const possible_firsts,
4536  std::vector<int>* const possible_lasts);
4537 
4538  // Applies the following sequence of ranks, ranks first, then rank
4539  // last. rank_first and rank_last represents different directions.
4540  // rank_first[0] corresponds to the first interval of the sequence.
4541  // rank_last[0] corresponds to the last interval of the sequence.
4542  // All intervals in the unperformed vector will be marked as such.
4543  void RankSequence(const std::vector<int>& rank_first,
4544  const std::vector<int>& rank_last,
4545  const std::vector<int>& unperformed);
4546 
4547  // Clears 'rank_first' and 'rank_last', and fills them with the
4548  // intervals in the order of the ranks. If all variables are ranked,
4549  // 'rank_first' will contain all variables, and 'rank_last' will
4550  // contain none.
4551  // 'unperformed' will contains all such interval variables.
4552  // rank_first and rank_last represents different directions.
4553  // rank_first[0] corresponds to the first interval of the sequence.
4554  // rank_last[0] corresponds to the last interval of the sequence.
4555  void FillSequence(std::vector<int>* const rank_first,
4556  std::vector<int>* const rank_last,
4557  std::vector<int>* const unperformed) const;
4558 
4559  // Returns the index_th interval of the sequence.
4560  IntervalVar* Interval(int index) const;
4561 
4562  // Returns the next of the index_th interval of the sequence.
4563  IntVar* Next(int index) const;
4564 
4565  // Returns the number of interval vars in the sequence.
4566  int64 size() const { return intervals_.size(); }
4567 
4568  // Accepts the given visitor.
4569  virtual void Accept(ModelVisitor* const visitor) const;
4570 
4571  private:
4572  int ComputeForwardFrontier();
4573  int ComputeBackwardFrontier();
4574  void UpdatePrevious() const;
4575 
4576  const std::vector<IntervalVar*> intervals_;
4577  const std::vector<IntVar*> nexts_;
4578  mutable std::vector<int> previous_;
4579 };

4754 // ----- SequenceVarElement -----
4755 
4756 // The SequenceVarElement stores a partial representation of ranked
4757 // interval variables in the underlying sequence variable.
4758 // This representation consists of three vectors:
4759 // - the forward sequence. That is the list of interval variables
4760 // ranked first in the sequence. The first element of the backward
4761 // sequence is the first interval in the sequence variable.
4762 // - the backward sequence. That is the list of interval variables
4763 // ranked last in the sequence. The first element of the backward
4764 // sequence is the last interval in the sequence variable.
4765 // - The list of unperformed interval variables.
4766 // Furthermore, if all performed variables are ranked, then by
4767 // convention, the forward_sequence will contain all such variables
4768 // and the backward_sequence will be empty.
4769 class SequenceVarElement : public AssignmentElement {
4770  public:
4771  SequenceVarElement();
4772  explicit SequenceVarElement(SequenceVar* const var);
4773  void Reset(SequenceVar* const var);
4774  SequenceVarElement* Clone();
4775  void Copy(const SequenceVarElement& element);
4776  SequenceVar* Var() const { return var_; }
4777  void Store();
4778  void Restore();
4779  void LoadFromProto(
4780  const SequenceVarAssignment& sequence_var_assignment_proto);
4781  void WriteToProto(SequenceVarAssignment* sequence_var_assignment_proto) const;
4782 
4783  const std::vector<int>& ForwardSequence() const;
4784  const std::vector<int>& BackwardSequence() const;
4785  const std::vector<int>& Unperformed() const;
4786  void SetSequence(const std::vector<int>& forward_sequence,
4787  const std::vector<int>& backward_sequence,
4788  const std::vector<int>& unperformed);
4789  void SetForwardSequence(const std::vector<int>& forward_sequence);
4790  void SetBackwardSequence(const std::vector<int>& backward_sequence);
4791  void SetUnperformed(const std::vector<int>& unperformed);
4792  bool Bound() const {
4793  return forward_sequence_.size() + unperformed_.size() == var_->size();
4794  }
4795 
4796  std::string DebugString() const;
4797 
4798  bool operator==(const SequenceVarElement& element) const;
4799  bool operator!=(const SequenceVarElement& element) const {
4800  return !(*this == element);
4801  }
4802 
4803  private:
4804  bool CheckClassInvariants();
4805 
4806  SequenceVar* var_;
4807  std::vector<int> forward_sequence_;
4808  std::vector<int> backward_sequence_;
4809  std::vector<int> unperformed_;
4810 };
4811 
4812 // ----- Assignment element container -----
4813 
4814 template <class V, class E>
4815 class AssignmentContainer {
4816  public:
4817  AssignmentContainer() {}
4818  E* Add(V* var) {
4819  CHECK(var != nullptr);
4820  int index = -1;
4821  if (!Find(var, &index)) {
4822  return FastAdd(var);
4823  } else {
4824  return &elements_[index];
4825  }
4826  }
4827  // Adds element without checking its presence in the container.
4828  E* FastAdd(V* var) {
4829  DCHECK(var != nullptr);
4830  elements_.emplace_back(var);
4831  return &elements_.back();
4832  }
4833  // Advanced usage: Adds element at a given position; position has to have
4834  // been allocated with AssignmentContainer::Resize() beforehand.
4835  E* AddAtPosition(V* var, int position) {
4836  elements_[position].Reset(var);
4837  return &elements_[position];
4838  }
4839  void Clear() {
4840  elements_.clear();
4841  if (!elements_map_.empty()) { // 2x speedup on OR-tools.
4842  elements_map_.clear();
4843  }
4844  }
4845  // Advanced usage: Resizes the container, potentially adding elements with
4846  // null variables.
4847  void Resize(size_t size) { elements_.resize(size); }
4848  bool Empty() const { return elements_.empty(); }
4849  // Copies the elements of 'container' which are already in the calling
4850  // container.
4851  void CopyIntersection(const AssignmentContainer<V, E>& container) {
4852  for (int i = 0; i < container.elements_.size(); ++i) {
4853  const E& element = container.elements_[i];
4854  const V* const var = element.Var();
4855  int index = -1;
4856  if (i < elements_.size() && elements_[i].Var() == var) {
4857  index = i;
4858  } else if (!Find(var, &index)) {
4859  continue;
4860  }
4861  DCHECK_GE(index, 0);
4862  E* const local_element = &elements_[index];
4863  local_element->Copy(element);
4864  if (element.Activated()) {
4865  local_element->Activate();
4866  } else {
4867  local_element->Deactivate();
4868  }
4869  }
4870  }
4871  // Copies all the elements of 'container' to this container, clearing its
4872  // previous content.
4873  void Copy(const AssignmentContainer<V, E>& container) {
4874  Clear();
4875  for (int i = 0; i < container.elements_.size(); ++i) {
4876  const E& element = container.elements_[i];
4877  FastAdd(element.Var())->Copy(element);
4878  }
4879  }
4880  bool Contains(const V* const var) const {
4881  int index;
4882  return Find(var, &index);
4883  }
4884  E* MutableElement(const V* const var) {
4885  E* const element = MutableElementOrNull(var);
4886  DCHECK(element != nullptr)
4887  << "Unknown variable " << var->DebugString() << " in solution";
4888  return element;
4889  }
4890  E* MutableElementOrNull(const V* const var) {
4891  int index = -1;
4892  if (Find(var, &index)) {
4893  return MutableElement(index);
4894  }
4895  return nullptr;
4896  }
4897  const E& Element(const V* const var) const {
4898  const E* const element = ElementPtrOrNull(var);
4899  DCHECK(element != nullptr)
4900  << "Unknown variable " << var->DebugString() << " in solution";
4901  return *element;
4902  }
4903  const E* ElementPtrOrNull(const V* const var) const {
4904  int index = -1;
4905  if (Find(var, &index)) {
4906  return &Element(index);
4907  }
4908  return nullptr;
4909  }
4910  const std::vector<E>& elements() const { return elements_; }
4911  E* MutableElement(int index) { return &elements_[index]; }
4912  const E& Element(int index) const { return elements_[index]; }
4913  int Size() const { return elements_.size(); }
4914  void Store() {
4915  for (E& element : elements_) {
4916  element.Store();
4917  }
4918  }
4919  void Restore() {
4920  for (E& element : elements_) {
4921  if (element.Activated()) {
4922  element.Restore();
4923  }
4924  }
4925  }
4926  bool AreAllElementsBound() const {
4927  for (const E& element : elements_) {
4928  if (!element.Bound()) return false;
4929  }
4930  return true;
4931  }
4932 
4933  // Returns true if this and 'container' both represent the same V* -> E map.
4934  // Runs in linear time; requires that the == operator on the type E is well
4935  // defined.
4936  bool operator==(const AssignmentContainer<V, E>& container) const {
4937  // We may not have any work to do
4938  if (Size() != container.Size()) {
4939  return false;
4940  }
4941  // The == should be order-independent
4942  EnsureMapIsUpToDate();
4943  // Do not use the hash_map::== operator! It
4944  // compares both content and how the map is hashed (e.g., number of
4945  // buckets). This is not what we want.
4946  for (const E& element : container.elements_) {
4947  const int position =
4948  gtl::FindWithDefault(elements_map_, element.Var(), -1);
4949  if (position < 0 || elements_[position] != element) {
4950  return false;
4951  }
4952  }
4953  return true;
4954  }
4955  bool operator!=(const AssignmentContainer<V, E>& container) const {
4956  return !(*this == container);
4957  }
4958 
4959  private:
4960  void EnsureMapIsUpToDate() const {
4961  absl::flat_hash_map<const V*, int>* map =
4962  const_cast<absl::flat_hash_map<const V*, int>*>(&elements_map_);
4963  for (int i = map->size(); i < elements_.size(); ++i) {
4964  (*map)[elements_[i].Var()] = i;
4965  }
4966  }
4967  bool Find(const V* const var, int* index) const {
4968  // This threshold was determined from microbenchmarks on Nehalem platform.
4969  const size_t kMaxSizeForLinearAccess = 11;
4970  if (Size() <= kMaxSizeForLinearAccess) {
4971  // Look for 'var' in the container by performing a linear
4972  // search, avoiding the access to (and creation of) the elements
4973  // hash table.
4974  for (int i = 0; i < elements_.size(); ++i) {
4975  if (var == elements_[i].Var()) {
4976  *index = i;
4977  return true;
4978  }
4979  }
4980  return false;
4981  } else {
4982  EnsureMapIsUpToDate();
4983  DCHECK_EQ(elements_map_.size(), elements_.size());
4984  return gtl::FindCopy(elements_map_, var, index);
4985  }
4986  }
4987 
4988  std::vector<E> elements_;
4989  absl::flat_hash_map<const V*, int> elements_map_;
4990 };

5191 // ---------- Pack Constraint ----------
5192 
5193 class Pack : public Constraint {
5194  public:
5195  Pack(Solver* const s, const std::vector<IntVar*>& vars, int number_of_bins);
5196 
5197  ~Pack() override;
5198 
5199  // ----- Public API -----
5200 
5201  // Dimensions are additional constraints than can restrict what is
5202  // possible with the pack constraint. It can be used to set capacity
5203  // limits, to count objects per bin, to compute unassigned
5204  // penalties...
5205 
5206  // This dimension imposes that for all bins b, the weighted sum
5207  // (weights[i]) of all objects i assigned to 'b' is less or equal
5208  // 'bounds[b]'.
5209  void AddWeightedSumLessOrEqualConstantDimension(
5210  const std::vector<int64>& weights, const std::vector<int64>& bounds);
5211 
5212  // This dimension imposes that for all bins b, the weighted sum
5213  // (weights->Run(i)) of all objects i assigned to 'b' is less or
5214  // equal to 'bounds[b]'. Ownership of the callback is transferred to
5215  // the pack constraint.
5216  void AddWeightedSumLessOrEqualConstantDimension(
5217  Solver::IndexEvaluator1 weights, const std::vector<int64>& bounds);
5218 
5219  // This dimension imposes that for all bins b, the weighted sum
5220  // (weights->Run(i, b) of all objects i assigned to 'b' is less or
5221  // equal to 'bounds[b]'. Ownership of the callback is transferred to
5222  // the pack constraint.
5223  void AddWeightedSumLessOrEqualConstantDimension(
5224  Solver::IndexEvaluator2 weights, const std::vector<int64>& bounds);
5225 
5226  // This dimension imposes that for all bins b, the weighted sum
5227  // (weights[i]) of all objects i assigned to 'b' is equal to loads[b].
5228  void AddWeightedSumEqualVarDimension(const std::vector<int64>& weights,
5229  const std::vector<IntVar*>& loads);
5230 
5231  // This dimension imposes that for all bins b, the weighted sum
5232  // (weights->Run(i, b)) of all objects i assigned to 'b' is equal to
5233  // loads[b].
5234  void AddWeightedSumEqualVarDimension(Solver::IndexEvaluator2 weights,
5235  const std::vector<IntVar*>& loads);
5236 
5237  // This dimension imposes:
5238  // forall b in bins,
5239  // sum (i in items: usage[i] * is_assigned(i, b)) <= capacity[b]
5240  // where is_assigned(i, b) is true if and only if item i is assigned
5241  // to the bin b.
5242  //
5243  // This can be used to model shapes of items by linking variables of
5244  // the same item on parallel dimensions with an allowed assignment
5245  // constraint.
5246  void AddSumVariableWeightsLessOrEqualConstantDimension(
5247  const std::vector<IntVar*>& usage, const std::vector<int64>& capacity);
5248 
5249  // This dimension enforces that cost_var == sum of weights[i] for
5250  // all objects 'i' assigned to a bin.
5251  void AddWeightedSumOfAssignedDimension(const std::vector<int64>& weights,
5252  IntVar* const cost_var);
5253 
5254  // This dimension links 'count_var' to the actual number of bins used in the
5255  // pack.
5256  void AddCountUsedBinDimension(IntVar* const count_var);
5257 
5258  // This dimension links 'count_var' to the actual number of items
5259  // assigned to a bin in the pack.
5260  void AddCountAssignedItemsDimension(IntVar* const count_var);
5261  // ----- Internal API -----
5262 
5263  void Post() override;
5264  void ClearAll();
5265  void PropagateDelayed();
5266  void InitialPropagate() override;
5267  void Propagate();
5268  void OneDomain(int var_index);
5269  std::string DebugString() const override;
5270  bool IsUndecided(int var_index, int bin_index) const;
5271  void SetImpossible(int var_index, int bin_index);
5272  void Assign(int var_index, int bin_index);
5273  bool IsAssignedStatusKnown(int var_index) const;
5274  bool IsPossible(int var_index, int bin_index) const;
5275  IntVar* AssignVar(int var_index, int bin_index) const;
5276  void SetAssigned(int var_index);
5277  void SetUnassigned(int var_index);
5278  void RemoveAllPossibleFromBin(int bin_index);
5279  void AssignAllPossibleToBin(int bin_index);
5280  void AssignFirstPossibleToBin(int bin_index);
5281  void AssignAllRemainingItems();
5282  void UnassignAllRemainingItems();
5283  // Accepts the given visitor.
5284  void Accept(ModelVisitor* const visitor) const override;
5285 
5286  private:
5287  bool IsInProcess() const;
5288  const std::vector<IntVar*> vars_;
5289  const int bins_;
5290  std::vector<Dimension*> dims_;
5291  std::unique_ptr<RevBitMatrix> unprocessed_;
5292  std::vector<std::vector<int>> forced_;
5293  std::vector<std::vector<int>> removed_;
5294  std::vector<IntVarIterator*> holes_;
5295  uint64 stamp_;
5296  Demon* demon_;

5299  bool in_process_;
